.TH HSH 1 "December 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a simple command line interpreter that executes commands
read from standard input.

Commands can be executed using absolute paths or searched for
in the PATH environment variable.

The shell supports both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH BUILTINS
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment variables.

.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell with an optional status.

.SH USAGE
The shell works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.PP
$ ./hsh
.PP
($) ls
.PP
($) env
.PP
($) exit

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Yara and Manar.

